Didier Drogba has 15 goals in 15 games for Chelsea against Arsenal, averaging one every 78 minutes. Drogba's first goals against came in the 2005 Community Shield, scoring both as Chelsea beat Arsenal 2-1. It was the 2005 Community Shield when he first put Arsenal to the sword, lashing two goals past Jens Lehmann in a 2-1 victory at the Millennium Stadium before scoring the decisive goal in a 1-0 victory in the Premier League three weeks later.